      	<h2>About Me</h2>
      	<p>Hello! My name is Adam, and I am currently a PhD student studying in the Department of Statistics at the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor. I'm interested in figuring out methods for learning about and improving the social and political world we inhabit, and also other stuff that's cool.</p> 
	<p>In my spare time, I like to read about politics, history, and mythology, watch foreign films, play around with computers, and go hiking.</p>
      	<p>I recieved my B.A. in Quantitative Economics and Sociology from the University of California, Irvine in 2011. I am a member of Golden Key and Phi Beta Kappa, and a recipient of the Rackham Merit Fellowship.</p>
